  "prompt": "Which is the best camera phone in the range of 15-18k?",
  "response": "The \"best\" camera phone in the 15-18k range depends on your priorities, as different phones excel in different areas. However, here are some strong contenders and what they offer:\n\n**Strong All-Around Performers:**\n\n*   **Motorola G84 5G:**\n    *   **Pros:** Excellent value for money, Good camera system with OIS,  decent performance, Good battery life.\n    *   **Cons:** Not the absolute best in low light, Design is simple.\n    *   **Why it's good:** A solid all-rounder, good camera with OIS for better video recording and low-light shots.\n\n*   **Samsung Galaxy M34 5G:**\n    *   **Pros:** Good camera setup (especially for daytime photography), Vibrant AMOLED display, Large battery, Reliable Samsung brand.\n    *   **Cons:** Average performance for gaming, Software can be a bit bloated.\n    *   **Why it's good:** A popular choice for its camera and overall reliability. Good for everyday photography and multimedia consumption.\n\n**Things to Consider:**\n\n*   **Megapixels (MP) are not everything:** Don't focus solely on the megapixel count. Sensor size, image processing, and lens quality are more important.\n*   **Video Recording:** Check for features like OIS (Optical Image Stabilization) and 4K recording.\n*   **Front Camera:** If you take a lot of selfies, pay attention to the front camera's specifications and features.\n*   **Low Light Performance:** Read reviews to see how well the camera performs in dimly lit environments.\n*   **Software and Image Processing:** Different manufacturers have different approaches to image processing. Some prefer a more natural look, while others boost colors and contrast.\n*   **Personal Preference:** Consider what type of photos you like to take (landscapes, portraits, macro, etc.) and choose a phone that excels in those areas.\n\n**Where to Buy:**\n\n*   Amazon\n*   Flipkart\n*   Offline Retail Stores (Croma, Vijay Sales, etc.)\n\n**Recommendation:**\n\nGiven the price range and overall balance, the **Motorola G84 5G** is a great option. However, I highly suggest checking reviews on sites like Gadgets360, GSMArena, and YouTube to see real-world camera samples and comparisons before making your final decision. Read and watch multiple reviews to get a balanced perspective.\n",
